msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:176
msgid "Three discrepancies were identified during implementation."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:178
msgid "**Issue 1 — Session token extraction from `/connect` (fixed)**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:180
msgid ""
"The spec defines the `/connect` response as returning the session token via "
"a `Set-Cookie` header, not `X-DM-DST`. The security scheme confirms that `X-"
"DM-DST` is the header used on _subsequent requests_, with the note that the "
"token value is found under \"HEADERS\" in the connect response. The `private "
"async connect()` method in `edocs.service.ts` was updated to parse `Set-"
"Cookie` and handle both the cookie-value format and a direct `X-DM-DST` "
"header as a fallback, covering any server-side variation between eDOCS "
"versions."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:182
msgid ""
"private async connect(): Promise<void> {\n"
"  // ...\n"
"  const response = await this.client.post('/connect', {\n"
"    data: {\n"
"      userid: config.edocs.userId,\n"
"      password: config.edocs.password,\n"
"      library: config.edocs.library,\n"
"    },\n"
"  });\n"
"\n"
"  // The spec returns the session token as Set-Cookie on /connect.\n"
"  // Extract the token value from the first cookie.\n"
"  const setCookie = response.headers['set-cookie'];\n"
"  const cookieHeader = Array.isArray(setCookie) ? setCookie[0] : setCookie;\n"
"  const token = cookieHeader?.split(';')[0]?.split('=').slice(1).join('=') "
"?? undefined;\n"
"\n"
"  if (!token) {\n"
"    throw new Error(\n"
"      'eDOCS connect() succeeded but no session token found in Set-Cookie "
"response header'\n"
"    );\n"
"  }\n"
"\n"
"  this.sessionToken = token;\n"
"  logger.info('Connected to eDOCS — session token cached');\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:211
msgid ""
"**Issue 2 — `_restapi.ref` for workspace linking in document upload "
"(unverified)**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:213
msgid ""
"The `UploadData` schema in the spec only documents `_restapi: { form_name: "
"\"...\" }`. The `ref` object used to link an uploaded document to a "
"workspace (`_restapi.ref.type = \"workspace\"`) is documented for the `/"
"urls` endpoint but not explicitly for `/documents`. It is expected to work "
"in practice — this is a known eDOCS REST API pattern — but must be confirmed "
"against a live DOCUVITT server when credentials become available."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:215
msgid "**Issue 3 — `CollectionResponse` shape (no action required)**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ccopilot-studio-edocs.md:217
msgid ""
"The spec defines `CollectionResponse → data → { set: {...}, list: [...] }`. "
"The service correctly navigates this as `response.data?.data?.list`, where "
"the outer `.data` is the HTTP response body and the inner `.data.list` "
"follows the spec's structure."
msgstr ""

