#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:256
msgid "Common issues"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:258
msgid ""
"**Keycloak Admin Console shows no realm**\n"
"The realm import runs on first start only. If the container was started "
"before `config/keycloak/ronl-realm.json` was present, run `npm run "
"docker:down:volumes && npm run docker:up`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:261
msgid ""
"**JWT audience error on API calls**\n"
"In Keycloak Admin: `Clients → ronl-business-api → Client scopes → ronl-"
"business-api-dedicated → Mappers → Add mapper → Audience → Save`. Then log "
"out and back in."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:264
msgid ""
"**Roles not appearing in JWT**\n"
"In Keycloak Admin: same path as above → Add mapper → `User Realm Role` → "
"Save. Log out and back in."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:267
msgid ""
"**CORS error in browser**\n"
"Verify `CORS_ORIGIN` in `packages/backend/.env` matches the frontend URL "
"exactly (including port)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:270
msgid "For additional issues, see [Troubleshooting]{1}."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cmcp-ai-assistant.md:1
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api\\developer\\mcp-ai-assistant.md:1"
msgid "MCP AI Assistant"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cmcp-ai-assistant.md:3
msgid ""
"The AI Assistant is a streaming chat interface embedded in the Gereedschap "
"tab of the caseworker dashboard. It connects a configurable LLM to a "
"registry of data sources via the [Model Context Protocol]{1} (MCP), allowing "
"caseworkers to query process definitions, running instances, tasks, "
"decisions, deployments, legislation, knowledge graph data, and deployed "
"process bundles in natural language."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cmcp-ai-assistant.md:5
msgid ""
"Sources and models are selected per session. See [LLM Provider Architecture]"
"{1} for how providers and models are registered and extended."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cmcp-ai-assistant.md:19
msgid "Data sources"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cmcp-ai-assistant.md:21
msgid ""
"The AI assistant connects to one or more **MCP providers** registered in "
"`McpRegistry`. Each provider exposes a curated set of read-only tools and "
"contributes a section to the system prompt. The frontend fetches the list of "
"providers from `GET /v1/mcp/sources` on mount and pre-selects all connected "
"ones. The user can deselect sources before sending a message."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cmcp-ai-assistant.md:28
msgid ""
"Four providers are registered. Each is independently enabled via its env var "
"and appears in `GET /v1/mcp/sources` only when connected."
msgstr ""

