"`processDefinition_getByKey`, `processInstance_list`, "
"`processInstance_count`, `processInstance_get`, `task_list`, `task_count`, "
"`task_getById`, `decision_list`, `decision_getByKey`, `deployment_list`, "
"`deployment_count`, `deployment_getById`, `incident_list`, `incident_count`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cmcp-ai-assistant.md:45
msgid ""
"All other `operaton-mcp` tools are blocked by the `ALLOWED_TOOLS` set in "
"`OperatonMcpProvider.ts`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cmcp-ai-assistant.md:47
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api\\developer\\mcp-ai-assistant.md:47"
msgid "Access pattern"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cmcp-ai-assistant.md:49
msgid ""
"The MCP AI Assistant uses [**Pattern 2 — `operaton-mcp` via `engine-rest`**]"
"{1} from the Operaton Access Patterns reference. The `operaton-mcp` "
"subprocess talks **directly to Operaton's `engine-rest` API**, bypassing the "
"RONL Business API entirely. It receives the full, unfiltered Operaton "
"surface — all process instances, all deployments, all tenants — with no "
"organisation filter applied."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cmcp-ai-assistant.md:51
msgid ""
"In `mcpClient.service.ts`, the `StdioClientTransport` spawns the `operaton-"
"mcp` child process and passes it the following env vars directly from the "
"backend configuration:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cmcp-ai-assistant.md:52
msgid ""
