msgid "Architecture"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-mcp-client.md:32
msgid ""
"Regular RONL Business API routes (`/v1/process`, `/v1/task`, `/v1/decision`) "
"enforce tenant isolation via `tenantMiddleware` — every request must carry a "
"`municipality` JWT claim and data is filtered to that organisation. This is "
"correct for human caseworkers but wrong for system actors such as an MCP "
"agent that needs a cross-organisation view of Operaton."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-mcp-client.md:34
msgid ""
"The M2M API solves this with a dedicated route group that applies only "
"`jwtMiddleware`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-mcp-client.md:36
msgid ""
"MCP Client / Automation tool\n"
"    │\n"
"    │  1. POST /token  (client_credentials)\n"
"    ▼\n"
"Keycloak (acc.keycloak.open-regels.nl)\n"
"    │\n"
"    │  2. access_token (JWT, aud: ronl-business-api)\n"
"    │     no municipality claim\n"
"    ▼\n"
"RONL Business API (acc.api.open-regels.nl)\n"
"    │  jwtMiddleware validates token\n"
"    │  no tenantMiddleware — no organisation filter\n"
"    ▼\n"
"Operaton (operaton-doc.open-regels.nl)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-mcp-client.md:55
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api\\developer\\operaton-mcp-client.md:55"
msgid "Keycloak client"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Coperaton-mcp-client.md:57
msgid ""
"A dedicated Keycloak client `operaton-mcp-client` is registered in the "
"`ronl` realm. It uses the **Client Credentials** grant — no browser redirect "
"or user login is involved. No `municipality` or `organisation_type` claims "
"are present in the token by design."
msgstr ""

