#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ctroubleshooting.md:163
msgid "DMN hit policy violation"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ctroubleshooting.md:165
msgid "**Symptom:**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ctroubleshooting.md:166
msgid ""
"POST /v1/decision/berekenrechtenhoogtezorg/evaluate → 500\n"
"{\n"
"  \"success\": false,\n"
"  \"error\": {\n"
"    \"code\": \"DECISION_EVALUATION_FAILED\",\n"
"    \"message\": \"DMN configuratiefout in beslissingstabel "
"'berekenrechtenhoogtezorg': meerdere regels zijn tegelijk van toepassing, "
"maar het trefriebeleid (hit policy) staat slechts één treffer toe. Neem "
"contact op met de beheerder.\"\n"
"  }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ctroubleshooting.md:177
msgid ""
"**Cause:** The DMN decision table uses the default `UNIQUE` hit policy, "
"which requires exactly one rule to match per evaluation. When multiple "
"disqualifying conditions are true simultaneously (e.g. both "
"`betalingsregeling = true` and `detentie = true`), two rules match and "
"Operaton throws a runtime exception. Operaton surfaces this as `\"Exception "
"while evaluating decision with key 'null'\"` — the `'null'` refers to the "
"internal rule key that could not be resolved, not to the decision key itself."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ctroubleshooting.md:179
msgid ""
"**Fix:** Open `BerekenRechtEnHoogteZorg.dmn` in Camunda Modeler and set the "
"hit policy on the decision table to `FIRST`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ctroubleshooting.md:180
msgid "<decisionTable id=\"decisionTable\" hitPolicy=\"FIRST\">"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ctroubleshooting.md:184
msgid ""
"With `FIRST`, rules are evaluated top-to-bottom and evaluation stops at the "
"first match. Ensure the disqualifying rules (betalingsregeling, detentie, "
"ingezetene, leeftijd, verzekering) appear above the income threshold rules "
"and the positive allowance rule."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ctroubleshooting.md:186
msgid ""
"Also correct the `Null` literals in all disqualifying output entries — the "
"FEEL spec requires lowercase `null`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ctroubleshooting.md:187
msgid ""
"<!-- Wrong -->\n"
"<outputEntry><text>Null</text></outputEntry>\n"
"\n"
"<!-- Correct -->\n"
"<outputEntry><text>null</text></outputEntry>"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ctroubleshooting.md:195
msgid ""
"After editing, redeploy the DMN to Operaton via the Camunda Modeler deploy "
"feature or the Operaton REST API."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ctroubleshooting.md:197
msgid ""
"**Error message routing:** The `operaton.service.ts` catch block detects "
"this specific error pattern and throws a descriptive `Error` instead of re-"
"throwing the raw axios exception. `decision.routes.ts` propagates that "
"message as `error.message` in the 500 response body. The frontend `api.ts` "
"reads `error.response.data` on a 500 and returns it as a structured "
"`ApiResponse`, so `Dashboard.tsx` renders `result.error.message` directly. "
"Citizens see a neutral notification; caseworkers see the technical message."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Ctroubleshooting.md:199
