#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cauthentication-iam.md:1
msgid "Authentication & IAM"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cauthentication-iam.md:3
msgid ""
"RONL Business API uses **Keycloak 23** as its Identity and Access Management "
"layer, implementing the OIDC Authorization Code Flow. Keycloak acts as an "
"identity broker, federating authentication requests to DigiD, eIDAS, and "
"eHerkenning — the three Dutch government identity providers."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cauthentication-iam.md:12
msgid "Authentication flows"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cauthentication-iam.md:14
msgid ""
"The platform supports two distinct authentication paths. Both converge at "
"the Business API's JWT validation middleware, but differ entirely in how the "
"user reaches Keycloak."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cauthentication-iam.md:16
msgid "Citizen flow (DigiD / eHerkenning / eIDAS)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cauthentication-iam.md:18
msgid ""
"Citizens select one of three identity providers on the landing page. "
"`AuthCallback` calls `keycloak.init({ onLoad: 'login-required', idpHint })`, "
"which redirects the browser directly to the selected external IdP — "
"bypassing Keycloak's native login form entirely."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cauthentication-iam.md:20
msgid ""
"sequenceDiagram\n"
"    participant B as Citizen (Browser)\n"
"    participant LC as LoginChoice.tsx\n"
"    participant AC as AuthCallback.tsx\n"
"    participant KC as Keycloak IAM\n"
"    participant IDP as DigiD / eHerkenning / eIDAS\n"
"    participant API as Business API\n"
"    participant BPM as Operaton BPMN Engine\n"
"\n"
"    B->>LC: Click DigiD / eHerkenning / eIDAS button\n"
"    LC->>LC: sessionStorage.set('selected_idp', 'digid')\n"
"    LC->>AC: navigate('/auth')\n"
"    AC->>KC: keycloak.init({ onLoad: 'login-required', idpHint: 'digid' })\n"
"    KC->>IDP: SAML AuthnRequest (via idpHint redirect)\n"
"    IDP->>B: Identity provider authentication UI\n"
"    B->>IDP: Credentials + MFA (if required)\n"
"    IDP->>KC: SAML Assertion (signed)\n"
"    KC->>KC: Validate assertion, map BSN / KvK / LoA attributes\n"
"    KC->>B: OIDC Authorization Code (redirect to /auth)\n"
"    B->>KC: Token request (code exchange)\n"
"    KC->>B: access_token + id_token (JWT)\n"
"    B->>API: REST call — Authorization: Bearer JWT\n"
"    API->>KC: Validate token (JWKS endpoint)\n"
"    API->>BPM: Start process with user context\n"
"    BPM-->>API: Process result\n"
"    API-->>B: Business response"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cauthentication-iam.md:49
msgid "Caseworker flow (Keycloak native)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cauthentication-iam.md:51
msgid ""
"Caseworkers are municipal employees whose accounts are managed directly in "
"the Keycloak `ronl` realm. They do not authenticate through an external IdP. "
"`AuthCallback` calls `keycloak.init({ onLoad: 'check-sso' })` first — a "
"silent check that avoids forcing a login screen if the caseworker already "
"has an active SSO session. Only if no session is found does Keycloak "
"redirect to its native login form."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cauthentication-iam.md:53
msgid ""
"sequenceDiagram\n"
"    participant B as Caseworker (Browser)\n"
"    participant LC as LoginChoice.tsx\n"
"    participant AC as AuthCallback.tsx\n"
"    participant KC as Keycloak IAM\n"
"    participant API as Business API\n"
"    participant BPM as Operaton BPMN Engine\n"
"\n"
"    B->>LC: Click \"Inloggen als Medewerker\"\n"
"    LC->>LC: sessionStorage.set('selected_idp', 'medewerker')\n"
"    LC->>AC: navigate('/auth')\n"
"    AC->>KC: keycloak.init({ onLoad: 'check-sso' })\n"
"    alt SSO session already exists\n"
"        KC-->>AC: authenticated = true\n"
"        AC->>B: navigate('/dashboard')\n"
"    else No SSO session\n"
"        KC-->>AC: authenticated = false\n"
"        AC->>KC: keycloak.login({ loginHint: '__medewerker__' })\n"
"        KC->>B: Keycloak login form (with caseworker banner)\n"
"        B->>KC: Username + password\n"
"        KC->>KC: Validate credentials, issue token\n"
"        KC->>B: OIDC Authorization Code (redirect to /auth)\n"
"        B->>KC: Token request (code exchange)\n"
"        KC->>B: access_token + id_token (JWT, roles: [\"caseworker\"])\n"
"        AC->>B: navigate('/dashboard')\n"
"    end\n"
"    B->>API: REST call — Authorization: Bearer JWT\n"
"    API->>KC: Validate token (JWKS endpoint)\n"
"    API->>BPM: Start process with caseworker context\n"
"    BPM-->>API: Process result\n"
"    API-->>B: Business response"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cauthentication-iam.md:87
msgid "Caseworker sentinel pattern"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cauthentication-iam.md:89
msgid ""
"The `loginHint: '__medewerker__'` value passed to `keycloak.login()` is a "
"sentinel — a known string that carries no real authentication meaning but "
"acts as a signal to the Keycloak theme. Keycloak passes `login_hint` to the "
"login page as the `login.username` variable, which the `login.ftl` "
"FreeMarker template reads at render time:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cauthentication-iam.md:91
msgid ""
"<#assign isMedewerker = (login.username!'') == '__medewerker__'>\n"
"\n"
"<#if isMedewerker>\n"
"<div id=\"kc-context-banner\" class=\"kc-context-medewerker\">\n"
"    <!-- briefcase icon -->\n"
"    Inloggen als gemeentemedewerker\n"
"</div>\n"
"</#if>\n"
"\n"
"<input ... value=\"<#if !isMedewerker>${(login.username!'')}</#if>\" ... />"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cauthentication-iam.md:104
msgid ""
"When `isMedewerker` is true, the template renders the indigo context banner "
"and suppresses the sentinel from the username field so the caseworker enters "
"their own credentials into an empty field. No JavaScript is required — the "
"suppression happens server-side in FreeMarker before the HTML is sent to the "
"browser."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cauthentication-iam.md:108
msgid "Keycloak as identity broker"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cauthentication-iam.md:110
msgid ""
"Keycloak sits between the municipality portal and the external identity "
"providers. It handles:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cauthentication-iam.md:112
