msgid "Issuance of OIDC tokens with custom claims (see below)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cauthentication-iam.md:118
msgid ""
"In the current development environment, DigiD is **simulated** — test users "
"in the Keycloak realm substitute for a real DigiD connection. The "
"architecture is identical; only the external IdP step is replaced by direct "
"Keycloak credentials."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cauthentication-iam.md:120
msgid ""
"Caseworker accounts are an exception to the identity broker pattern. Because "
"municipal employees are managed directly in the `ronl` realm, their "
"authentication stays entirely within Keycloak — no SAML round-trip to an "
"external IdP occurs. The `municipality` and `caseworker` role attributes are "
"set directly on the user account in Keycloak Admin and included in the JWT "
"via protocol mappers."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cauthentication-iam.md:124
msgid "JWT token structure"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cauthentication-iam.md:126
msgid ""
"The Business API validates every request against the JWT access token. The "
"token contains standard OIDC claims plus RONL-specific custom claims added "
"by Keycloak protocol mappers:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cauthentication-iam.md:128
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"iss\": \"https://keycloak.open-regels.nl/realms/ronl\",\n"
"  \"aud\": \"ronl-business-api\",\n"
"  \"sub\": \"user-uuid-123\",\n"
"  \"typ\": \"Bearer\",\n"
"  \"preferred_username\": \"test-citizen-utrecht\",\n"
"  \"municipality\": \"utrecht\",\n"
"  \"roles\": [\"citizen\"],\n"
"  \"loa\": \"substantial\"\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

