msgid ""
"Two suspension points — the process does not complete in a single request"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cbusiness-rules-execution.md:118
msgid ""
"Two actors — citizen initiates, caseworker drives both decision and "
"notification"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cbusiness-rules-execution.md:119
msgid ""
"Subprocess — the material decision happens inside "
"`TreeFellingPermitSubProcess`, which writes its variables back to the AWB "
"shell"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cbusiness-rules-execution.md:120
msgid ""
"No result in the start response — the citizen receives only a "
"`dossierReference`; the actual decision is only available later via `/v1/"
"process/history`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cbusiness-rules-execution.md:122
msgid ""
"From v2.2.0, citizen and caseworker interaction with the AWB process is "
"driven entirely by **Camunda Forms** — JSON schemas authored in the [LDE "
"Form Editor]{1} and deployed alongside the BPMN in Operaton. The citizen "
"start form is fetched and rendered dynamically; the caseworker review and "
"notification forms are fetched per task. A **Decision Viewer** in the "
"citizen dashboard fetches the final variable state of completed applications "
"via the Operaton history API. See [Dynamic Forms]{2} for the full "
"implementation detail."
msgstr ""

