msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccaseworker-dashboard.md:243
msgid "Tenant-scoped vs platform-scoped features"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccaseworker-dashboard.md:245
msgid ""
"Not all dashboard features are controlled by `tenants.json`. There are two "
"distinct categories:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccaseworker-dashboard.md:247
msgid ""
"**Tenant-scoped features** are configured per organisation in `tenants.json` "
"via `leftPanelSections`. They vary between tenants — a section present for "
"Flevoland may be absent for Utrecht. Adding or removing a tenant-scoped "
"feature requires only a `tenants.json` change; no code is touched."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccaseworker-dashboard.md:249
msgid ""
"**Platform-scoped features** are hardcoded in `CaseworkerDashboard.tsx` and "
"apply across all tenants. They are not controlled by organisation — instead, "
"visibility is gated by **role**. A platform-scoped feature is either present "
"for all tenants (if the user holds the required role) or absent for all "
"tenants (if they do not)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccaseworker-dashboard.md:251
msgid ""
"The **audit log** is the primary example of a platform-scoped feature. It is "
"not listed in any tenant's `leftPanelSections`, it shows cross-tenant data, "
"and its visibility is governed by the `admin` role — not by organisation."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccaseworker-dashboard.md:253
msgid ""
"The **Gereedschap** tab is a second example. It is also not in "
"`tenants.json` — it is a fixed top-nav page available to all authenticated "
"caseworkers regardless of organisation. It provides a central hub for "
"platform tools (LDE, TriplyDB, CPSV Editor, CPRMV API, Operaton Cockpit, "
"eDOCS, SAP, KMS), each as a tool card. Active tools open in a new tab; "
"placeholder tools (eDOCS, SAP, KMS) show an orange **Binnenkort** badge "
"instead. Live status widgets for Operaton, eDOCS, CPRMV API, TriplyDB, and "
"LDE are fetched on mount — eDOCS and Operaton via existing endpoints, the "
"three external tools via `GET /v1/health/external` (server-side HEAD "
"requests to avoid CORS). Operaton Cockpit and SAP are only visible to users "
"with the `admin` role. Adding a new tool requires a single entry in the "
"`PLATFORM_TOOLS` constant in `GereedschapSection.tsx`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccaseworker-dashboard.md:255
msgid ""
"Two further features follow the same pattern: the **Changelog button** in "
"the top navigation bar and **top navigation filtering** (which hides top-nav "
"pages that have no accessible sections for the current user). Both are "
"rendered unconditionally in `CaseworkerDashboard.tsx` and are unaffected by "
"tenant configuration."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccaseworker-dashboard.md:257
msgid ""
"The practical rule when adding new dashboard functionality: if the feature "
"is organisation-specific, add it to `tenants.json` and implement the "
"corresponding `case` in `renderContent()`. If the feature is cross-tenant "
"and role-gated, add it directly to `CaseworkerDashboard.tsx` without "
"touching `tenants.json`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccaseworker-dashboard.md:266
msgid "Platform-scoped vs tenant-scoped sections"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccaseworker-dashboard.md:268
msgid ""
"Not all top-nav tabs in the caseworker dashboard are equal. The dashboard "
"distinguishes two categories:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccaseworker-dashboard.md:270
msgid ""
"**Tenant-scoped sections** are driven entirely by `tenants.json`. The "
"`leftPanelSections` object per tenant defines which sections appear under "
"`home`, `personal-info`, and `projects`. Adding or removing a section for a "
"specific organisation requires only a change to `tenants.json` — no code "
"changes are needed. This makes it safe to roll out features incrementally "
"per organisation type."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccaseworker-dashboard.md:272
msgid ""
"**Platform-scoped sections** are hardcoded in `CaseworkerDashboard.tsx` and "
"are identical for all tenants. They are gated by role or authentication "
"state, not by organisation. The canonical examples are the `audit-log` and "
"`gereedschap` tabs."
msgstr ""

