msgid ""
"The `organisation_type` user attribute in Keycloak determines which category "
"a user belongs to. It is injected into every JWT as the `organisation_type` "
"claim via a protocol mapper and propagated through `AuthenticatedUser` into "
"all backend middleware and BPMN process variables."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccommercial-org-integration.md:25
msgid "Cross-tenant processing authority"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccommercial-org-integration.md:27
msgid ""
"A commercial organisation can surface government services — such as the AWB "
"zorgtoeslag application — within its own branded portal. The government "
"authority responsible for the actual processing is a separate national "
"tenant."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccommercial-org-integration.md:31
msgid "For zorgtoeslag this works as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccommercial-org-integration.md:33
msgid ""
"Citizen (municipality = unive)\n"
"    ↓ logs in via DigiD, enters Unive MijnOmgeving\n"
"    ↓ submits AwbZorgtoeslagProcess via ProcessStartFormViewer\n"
"Backend POST /v1/process/AwbZorgtoeslagProcess/start\n"
"    ↓ overrides municipality variable → \"toeslagen\"\n"
"    ↓ records originTenantId → \"unive\"\n"
"Operaton (AwbZorgtoeslagProcess instance, municipality = toeslagen)\n"
"    ↓ caseworker task queue filtered by municipality = toeslagen\n"
"test-caseworker-toeslagen picks up the task\n"
"    ↓ completes AWB review phases\n"
"Decision document available\n"
"    ↓ citizen reads it from Unive MijnOmgeving via applicantId ownership "
"check"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccommercial-org-integration.md:48
msgid ""
"The key design principle is that **the channel and the processing authority "
"are decoupled**. The citizen never leaves the Unive MijnOmgeving, but the "
"dossier is handled entirely by Dienst Toeslagen."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccommercial-org-integration.md:52
msgid "Processing authority override"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccommercial-org-integration.md:54
msgid ""
"The `POST /v1/process/:key/start` route applies a per-process-key override "
"for `AwbZorgtoeslagProcess`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccommercial-org-integration.md:57
msgid ""
"`municipality` is set to `toeslagen` regardless of the requesting user's "
"tenant"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccommercial-org-integration.md:58
msgid ""
"`originTenantId` records the originating channel (e.g. `unive`) for reporting"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccommercial-org-integration.md:60
msgid ""
"This override runs after variable coercion and before forwarding to Operaton."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccommercial-org-integration.md:62
msgid "Cross-tenant access control"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccommercial-org-integration.md:64
msgid ""
"Two endpoints implement a dual-check access model to allow commercial org "
"citizens to read their own dossiers even when the underlying process ran "
"under a different processing authority:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccommercial-org-integration.md:68
msgid ""
"**`GET /v1/process/:id/historic-variables`** and **`GET /v1/process/"
":instanceId/decision-document`**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccommercial-org-integration.md:71
msgid "Access is granted when **either**:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccommercial-org-integration.md:73
msgid ""
"`municipality` on the process matches the requesting user's `tenantId` "
"(normal same-tenant access), **or**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccommercial-org-integration.md:75
msgid ""
"`applicantId` on the process matches the requesting user's `userId` (citizen "
"self-access across tenant boundaries)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccommercial-org-integration.md:78
msgid ""
"This means a Unive citizen can read their own zorgtoeslag decision document. "
"A Toeslagen caseworker can still access all processes in their municipality "
"scope. No other tenant can cross boundaries."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccommercial-org-integration.md:82
msgid "History endpoint"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Ccommercial-org-integration.md:84
msgid ""
"`GET /v1/process/history` normally filters by both `applicantId` and "
"`municipality`. For users with `organisationType = commercial` the "
"`municipality` filter is omitted, so the citizen's own dossiers are returned "
"regardless of which authority processed them."
msgstr ""

