"platform supports **commercial organisations** as a tenant category."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cmulti-tenant-portal.md:126
msgid ""
"A commercial tenant has its own branded MijnOmgeving and feature flags but "
"delegates AWB process handling to a designated government processing "
"authority. The `organisationType: \"commercial\"` value in `tenants.json` "
"and the corresponding `organisation_type: commercial` Keycloak user "
"attribute are the only configuration changes required. The rest of the "
"theming and feature flag system works identically to other tenant types. For "
"the full cross-tenant architecture — including the processing authority "
"override, cross-tenant history, and decision document access — see "
"[Commercial Organisation Integration]{1}."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:1
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api\\features\\overview.md:1"
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:5
msgid "The Business API Layer Pattern"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:7
msgid ""
"RONL Business API implements the **Business API Layer** pattern for "
"government digital services. This pattern provides a secure, audited "
"interface between a municipality's IAM system and the Operaton BPMN engine."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:9
msgid "The challenge"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:11
msgid ""
"Dutch municipalities need to offer digital services to residents that "
"satisfy:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:13
msgid ""
"**DigiD / eIDAS / eHerkenning** authentication (government-grade security)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:14
msgid ""
"**Multi-tenancy** — each municipality has its own users, data, and branding"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:15
msgid "**Compliance** — BIO, NEN 7510, AVG/GDPR requirements"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:16
msgid "**Audit logging** — a complete trail of all actions"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:17
msgid "**Reliability** — comparable to formally certified government services"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:19
msgid "The integration pattern"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:21
msgid ""
"Resident\n"
"   ↓\n"
"Municipality Portal (MijnOmgeving)\n"
"   ↓  (DigiD, eIDAS, eHerkenning)\n"
"Keycloak IAM\n"
"   ↓  (OIDC / JWT / signed claims)\n"
"Business API Layer  ← RONL sits here\n"
"   ↓  (authenticated REST)\n"
"Operaton BPMN Engine"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:33
msgid ""
"The Business API Layer sits between Keycloak and Operaton, handling all "
"security and business logic before any request reaches the execution engine."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:35
msgid "Why not expose Operaton directly?"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:37
msgid ""
"Operaton's native REST API does not perform JWT validation, does not enforce "
"multi-tenant isolation, does not emit audit logs in a compliance-grade "
"format, and is not designed for public exposure. Fronting it with RONL "
"Business API addresses all of these concerns without modifying the engine "
"itself."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:41
msgid "Core responsibilities"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:43
msgid ""
"**Token validation** — validates OIDC/JWT tokens issued by Keycloak, "
"verifying the signature against JWKS, checking expiration, and confirming "
"the audience claim matches `ronl-business-api`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:45
msgid ""
"**Claims mapping** — converts JWT custom claims into Operaton process "
"variables. The claim `municipality` becomes the tenant context; `roles` "
"drives authorization decisions; `loa` (Level of Assurance) gates access to "
"sensitive operations."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:47
msgid ""
"**Authorization** — enforces per-municipality access rules and validates "
"that the user's role permits the requested action (e.g. caseworkers can "
"process applications, citizens can only view their own)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:49
msgid ""
"**Tenant isolation** — ensures that a caseworker from Utrecht cannot read "
"process instances belonging to Amsterdam. All queries are filtered by the "
"`municipality` claim extracted from the JWT."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:51
msgid ""
"**Process invocation** — calls Operaton's REST API with the validated user "
"context injected as process variables, hiding BPMN complexity behind a clean "
"REST interface."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:53
msgid ""
"**Audit logging** — writes a tamper-evident audit entry for every API call, "
"recording who performed what action and when. Stored in Azure PostgreSQL "
"with 7-year retention."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:55
msgid ""
"**API simplification** — presents a versioned (`/v1/*`) REST API following "
"the Dutch Government API Design Rules (API-05, API-20, API-57), hiding "
"Operaton's internal API structure from municipality frontends."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:59
msgid "Example flow: zorgtoeslag calculation"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:61
msgid ""
"1.  Resident visits https://mijn.open-regels.nl (Utrecht portal)\n"
"2.  Frontend detects no valid JWT → redirects to Keycloak\n"
"3.  Keycloak authenticates (DigiD simulation) → issues JWT:\n"
"      { \"municipality\": \"utrecht\", \"roles\": [\"citizen\"], \"loa\": "
"\"substantial\" }\n"
"4.  Frontend submits calculation:\n"
"      POST /v1/calculations/zorgtoeslag\n"
"      Authorization: Bearer <JWT>\n"
"      { \"income\": 24000, \"age\": 25, \"healthInsurance\": true }\n"
"5.  Backend validates JWT signature against JWKS endpoint\n"
"6.  Maps claims → process variables:\n"
"      { \"initiator\": \"user-uuid\", \"municipality\": \"utrecht\",\n"
"        \"input\": { \"inkomenEnVermogen\": 24000, \"18JaarOfOuder\": true, "
"... } }\n"
"7.  Calls Operaton: POST /process-definition/key/zorgtoeslag/start\n"
"8.  Operaton executes BPMN workflow and evaluates DMN rules\n"
"9.  Backend writes audit log entry\n"
"10. Returns to frontend: { \"eligible\": true, \"amount\": 1150 }"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:82
msgid "Open source components"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Coverview.md:84
msgid ""
"RONL Business API uses exclusively open source components under government-"
"compatible licences."
