#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cregelcatalogus.md:1
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api\\features\\regelcatalogus.md:1"
msgid "Regelcatalogus"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cregelcatalogus.md:3
msgid ""
"From v2.5.0, the RONL Business API caseworker dashboard includes a "
"**Regelcatalogus** — a public-facing section that exposes the RONL knowledge "
"graph directly inside MijnOmgeving, without requiring a caseworker login. It "
"draws on five parallel SPARQL queries against the RONL TriplyDB endpoint and "
"presents services, organisations, concepts, and implementation rules in a "
"tabbed interface."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cregelcatalogus.md:12
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api\\features\\regelcatalogus.md:12"
msgid "Placement and access"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cregelcatalogus.md:14
msgid ""
"The Regelcatalogus appears as a third item under the **Home** tab in the "
"caseworker dashboard left panel. It is declared with `\"isPublic\": true` in "
"`tenants.json`, so it is visible to unauthenticated visitors alongside "
"Nieuws and Berichten."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cregelcatalogus.md:16
msgid ""
"The section is rendered by the `RegelCatalogus` React component (`src/"
"components/CaseWorkerDashboard/RegelCatalogus.tsx`), which calls `GET /v1/"
"public/regelcatalogus` on mount and distributes the response across four "
"internal tabs."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cregelcatalogus.md:20
msgid "The four tabs"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cregelcatalogus.md:22
msgid ""
"From v2.9.2 the tabs render in this order: **Organisaties**, **Diensten**, "
"**Regels**, **Concepten**."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cregelcatalogus.md:24
msgid "Organisaties"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cregelcatalogus.md:26
msgid ""
"Implementing organisations are listed with their logo (resolved via the "
"TriplyDB assets API to a versioned CDN URL), homepage link, and the services "
"they implement. The same logo resolution mechanism is used in the Linked "
"Data Explorer."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cregelcatalogus.md:33
msgid "Diensten"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cregelcatalogus.md:35
msgid ""
"Public services from the RONL knowledge graph are shown as expandable cards. "
"Each card displays the service title, a full description, and a link to the "
"service URI in TriplyDB. Clicking **Toon concepten** navigates directly to "
"the Concepten tab with that service pre-selected as a filter."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cregelcatalogus.md:37
msgid "Regels"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cregelcatalogus.md:39
msgid ""
"Implementation rules are grouped by service. Each group is collapsible. A "
"search input filters across all groups simultaneously; matching groups "
"expand automatically. Each rule entry shows the rule title, optional "
"validity date, and an expandable description."
