msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:59
msgid "`caseworker-newtown`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:61
msgid ""
"Or, if using the municipality-prefixed role convention that the JWT "
"middleware already supports, simply add the generic `citizen` and "
"`caseworker` roles to new user accounts with an attribute `municipality = "
"newtown`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:63
msgid "**Add the municipality attribute mapper:**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:65
msgid ""
"The `municipality` claim in the JWT is populated by a Keycloak protocol "
"mapper on the `ronl-business-api` client. Verify the mapper named "
"`municipality` exists under:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:67
msgid ""
"Clients → ronl-business-api → Client scopes\n"
"  → ronl-business-api-dedicated → Mappers → municipality"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cadding-municipality.md:72
msgid ""
"The mapper reads the `municipality` user attribute and injects it into the "
"access token. Set `municipality = newtown` on each user account belonging to "
"the new municipality."
msgstr ""

