"and one for caseworkers."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:35
msgid "Step 2 — Choose your identity provider"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:37
msgid "Select the option that matches your credential:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:39
msgid ""
"**🟠 DigiD** (Digitale Identiteit) For Dutch residents. Requires a valid "
"DigiD account. Supports assurance levels basis, midden, and hoog."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:42
msgid ""
"**🔵 eHerkenning** For businesses and organisations. Requires an eHerkenning "
"account. Supports mandates (machtiging) for acting on behalf of an "
"organisation."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:45
msgid ""
"**🟣 eIDAS** For EU residents without DigiD. Cross-border authentication "
"compliant with the eIDAS regulation."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:48
msgid "Step 3 — Redirect to identity provider"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:50
msgid "After clicking a citizen button, `AuthCallback.tsx` calls:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:52
msgid ""
"keycloak.init({\n"
"  onLoad: 'login-required',\n"
"  checkLoginIframe: false,\n"
"  idpHint: 'digid' // or 'eherkenning' / 'eidas'\n"
"});"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:60
msgid ""
"The `idpHint` tells Keycloak to skip its own login form and redirect "
"immediately to the selected identity provider. In production, this takes you "
"directly to DigiD, eHerkenning, or the eIDAS network. In the test "
"environment (no real IdPs configured), Keycloak falls back to its native "
"username/password form without a context banner."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:67
msgid "Step 4 — Authenticate"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:69
msgid ""
"**DigiD:** Enter your DigiD username and password. Complete two-factor "
"authentication if your assurance level requires it."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:71
msgid ""
"**eHerkenning:** Enter your eHerkenning credentials. Optionally select a "
"mandate if acting on behalf of an organisation."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:73
msgid ""
"**eIDAS:** Authenticate through your EU member state's identity provider."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:75
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api\\user-guide\\login-flow.md:75"
msgid "Step 5 — Token issuance"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:77
msgid ""
"After successful authentication, Keycloak validates the identity provider "
"response, maps user attributes (BSN for DigiD, KvK number for eHerkenning, "
"eIDAS PersonIdentifier), applies municipality settings, and issues a signed "
"JWT access token."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:79
msgid "**Example JWT payload (citizen):**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:81
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"sub\": \"abc123def456\",\n"
"  \"name\": \"Jan de Vries\",\n"
"  \"preferred_username\": \"test-citizen-utrecht\",\n"
"  \"municipality\": \"utrecht\",\n"
"  \"loa\": \"hoog\",\n"
"  \"realm_access\": {\n"
"    \"roles\": [\"citizen\"]\n"
"  },\n"
"  \"aud\": \"ronl-business-api\",\n"
"  \"iss\": \"https://acc.keycloak.open-regels.nl/realms/ronl\",\n"
"  \"exp\": 1708534800,\n"
"  \"iat\": 1708533900\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:98
msgid "Step 6 — Dashboard"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:100
msgid ""
"The portal receives the JWT and displays the citizen dashboard with "
"municipality-specific theming and the zorgtoeslag calculator. The JWT is "
"valid for 15 minutes and refreshed automatically while the session is active."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:104
msgid "Caseworker login"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:106
msgid ""
"Caseworkers (medewerkers) are municipal employees managed directly in the "
"Keycloak realm. They do not authenticate through DigiD or eHerkenning — they "
"use Keycloak's native username/password form, which is visually "
"distinguished from the citizen login with a dedicated context banner."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:108
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api\\user-guide\\login-flow.md:108"
msgid "What you need"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:110
msgid ""
"A Keycloak account in the `ronl` realm with the `caseworker` role assigned"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cuser-guide%5Clogin-flow.md:111
msgid "The `municipality` attribute set to your municipality (e.g. `utrecht`)"
msgstr ""

